Tasty food...  Great service...  Prompt service...  Fair pricing...  Open during COVID-19 pandemic...  Social distancing & masking up!!!  I appreciate when I see a business post signs REQUIRING MASKS to be worn inside their facility; this lets me know they care about their employees & their customers... Hello & Yes!!!! #maskupBABY  This day, we stopped in for a bite to eat. As of late, not only is eating out a challenge due to the COVID-19 pandemic, but it is also a challenge because of my dietary restrictions.  Stopping into this restaurant was a no brainer. I immediately knew I would get a vegan burrito. And that is exactly what I had. Others  in my party had a shrimp bowl and a cheeseburger tortilla kids meal.  My food was properly prepared. The burrito was massive. I did not think I would finish it all, but I did. Can you say FAMISHED!!!! And in finishing it all, I was full for the rest of the day.  Loved stopping in to this restaurant. The vibrantly colored decor was very attractive and appealing to my eye. The social distancing markers on the floor allowed me to place an order and maintain my distance for safety sake.  Ordering was seamless. We placed our order. We paid via contactless payment processing. We waited about 10 minutes and our food was prepared then we were out of the door.  Love that the restaurant has hand sanitizers strategically placed inside. This gave me an additional security that the restaurant owner, employees and customers would all be safer.  I plan to return and get another HUGE MASSIVELY DELICIOUS UBER FILLING vegan burrito in the near future.

My mother and I came to this location about half an hour before they closed with the intentions to get something to-go. The manager was sitting in the dining section and an employee sat on the other side where majority of the chairs were already on the tables. We didn't think much of this and proceeded to the register to place our order. The two young men behind the counter looked ready to prepare our meals when the manager comes to them directing them to start cleaning. We wait another few minutes, still hadn't been greeted, and the other employee comes behind the counter and pushed a few buttons on the register which led us to believe he would be taking our orders. He then walked away, without speaking which prompted us to spend another minute contemplating our exit. When he returned less than 30 seconds later, he also began to clean his cooking station. At this point we decided to leave and on our way out the manager, who finally acknowledged us yells after us "I want some McDonald's too ladies!....."  Usually when we come here, the customer service is lacking but at least we're usually greeted and have our orders taken within a minute of entering. Needless to say, following this incident we have yet to return.

We went last night for a school fundraiser and everything was comically terrible. (This would be a one star review, but since they're helping our school, I'll give them a star for that- although next time, I'll give the $30 directly to the school and find some edible food elsewhere). When we arrived, the cashier began to take our order, then interrupted us to answer the phone. We hung out for 5 minutes while she argued with someone on the phone and the line got progressively longer and more chaotic. Each of our drinks from the soda fountain tasted like dirty pipes, which was a nice change because our food tasted like NOTHING. If you like bland food that tastes like burnt meat, topped with plain rice and wrapped in soggy flour, this place could be your new jam. If you like Mexican food- maybe go somewhere else? The silver lining is that, as a family, we got to share this terrible dinner together and bond over how truly awful everything was, so in my book that's kind of a win.
